    <body>Tricity is a metropolitan area in northern Poland (in Pomeranian Voivodeship), consisting of three cities: Gdańsk, Gdynia and Sopot, as well as minor towns in their vicinity. They are situated adjacent to one another, in a row on the coast of Gdańsk Bay, Baltic Sea, in Eastern or Gdansk Pomerania (often referred to as Pomerelia in English). The Tricity metropolitan area has a population of over 1 million people.</body>
